        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 28 at 12:52PM CDT by NWS Corpus Christi TX</headline>
        <description>At 1252 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Long Mott, or near Port Lavaca, moving northeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Alamo Beach, Olivia, Green Lake, Point Comfort, Indianola, Magnolia
Beach, Seadrift, Port Lavaca, Schicke Point, Port Alto, and Long
Mott.

This includes US Highway 87 between mile markers 836 and 840.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
